[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/RushConnectedPawns"]
[FEN "r4rk1/7p/bpn2pp1/p1p1p3/4P3/1P1B2P1/PBPP3P/R4RK1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2026.06.03"]
[UTCTime "23:54:54"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Let's start our journey on pawn structures with a simple and exaggerated example. Black to move, find his best move. }
1... Bxd3! 2. cxd3 $19 { Great find! In this position, the stand-out point is white's doubled pawns on the d-file. They are called doubled pawns because there are two pawns (hence the name 'doubled') on a file. These pawns can potentially become very weak. } *


[Event "Mastering Positional Chess!: Isolated Pawns🎓"]
[Date "2026.06.03"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
