[FEN "2rr4/pp2bkpp/3p4/2pN4/2P5/3K1P2/PP4PP/2RR4 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2026.06.03"]
[UTCTime "23:54:55"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ outpost🏰! An outpost in chess is any square that can't be attacked by an enemy pawn, for example, the d5-sqaure in this case. These squares are preferably occupied by knights, as in this case. Play f4 for more. }
1. f4 $16 { The knight on d5 is a menace to black because he can't get rid of it and it stares intently into his camp. } *


