[UTCDate "2026.06.03"]
[UTCTime "23:54:55"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Space in chess is basically the number of squares one side possesses. This advantage can mostly be accumulated by the pushing of pawns up the board. This advantage can be decisive in positions with many pieces, or even in endgames like this. }
23. e5! { White gains even more space and opens the position before black is ready. } *


