[FEN "r1rq1bk1/1n1b1p1p/3p1np1/1p1Pp3/1Pp1P3/2P1BNNP/R2Q1PP1/1B2R1K1 w - - 2 24"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2026.06.03"]
[UTCTime "23:54:55"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ The fight for open files is one of the ever-lasting topics in chess. The example on the board is probably the most famous example of occupying an open file. This topic also correlates with the previous one: Space. Find white's best move (and also what World Champion Karpov played). }
24. Ba7!! { Brilliant! Due to black's lack of space, he is helpless against the idea of doubling rooks on the a-file, and the bishop on a7 is like a huge boulder in black's path. Karpov went on to win cleanly in Karpov - Unzicker Nice 1974. } *


